frus:attachment.p:
Considering that it has not been proved that the laws of Texas demand the
                        autopsy as an element of proof of murders committed there, and that in this
                        country the district judge could not have seen the body of Maria Hernandez;
                        therefore, article 116 of the Code of Federal Penal Procedure shall lie in
                        the present case;

Considering that the Executive of Mexico does not think that there is any
                        especial reason to deny the extradition of Jimenez because of his Mexican
                        nationality;
